"title": "6183: ignorance, of God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6183: ignorance, of god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A lack of knowledge of God, regarded as inexcusable by Scripture. God has made his existence, nature and power known to all through creation. God himself is not ignorant of human sin, but is able to discern the real intentions of human minds and wills.</p>\n<h2>Ignorance of God is inexcusable</h2>\n<h3>God is made known through creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:18-Rom1:20\">ROM 1:18–1:20</a></strong> <em>As God is made known to all through nature, human ignorance of God is inexcusable.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:1-Ps19:4\">PSA 19:1–19:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:17\">ACT 14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24-Acts17:28\">ACT 17:24–17:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:14-Rom2:15\">ROM 2:14–2:15</a></p>\n<h3>God revealed himself to Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:13-Neh9:14\">NEH 9:13–9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:10-Exod19:11\">EXO 19:10–19:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:16-Exod19:19\">EXO 19:16–19:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:7\">PSA 103:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:19-Ps147:20\">PSA 147:19–147:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:5\">EZK 20:5</a></p>\n<h2>Ignorance of God is linked to sin and rebellion</h2>\n<h3>Among the Gentiles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:18-Eph4:19\">EPH 4:18–4:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:2\">EXO 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:22\">JHN 4:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:23\">ACT 17:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:3-1Thess4:5\">1TH 4:3–4:5</a></p>\n<h3>In Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:2-Isa1:3\">ISA 1:2–1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:10\">ISA 56:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:8-Jer2:9\">JER 2:8–2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:22\">JER 4:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:4-Jer5:5\">JER 5:4–5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:7-Jer8:12\">JER 8:7–8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:6\">JER 9:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:21\">JER 10:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:1\">HOS 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:6\">HOS 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:10\">AMO 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Ignorance of God in the ministry of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Among the religious leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:13-John8:19\">JHN 8:13–8:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:23-Matt22:32\">MAT 22:23–22:32</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:18-Mark12:27\">MRK 12:18–12:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:27-Luke20:38\">LUK 20:27–20:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:54-John8:55\">JHN 8:54–8:55</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:2-John16:3\">JHN 16:2–16:3</a></p>\n<h3>Among his disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:8-John14:11\">JHN 14:8–14:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31-Luke18:34\">LUK 18:31–18:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:5-John14:7\">JHN 14:5–14:7</a></p>\n<h2>God is not ignorant of human sin and motives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:5\">GEN 6:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:13\">HEB 4:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:7\">EXO 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:12-Job28:28\">JOB 28:12–28:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:1-Ps139:6\">PSA 139:1–139:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:5\">PSA 147:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:5\">EZK 11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:8\">MAT 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:24\">ACT 1:24</a></p>\n<h2>Human ignorance of sin and the revelation of God</h2>\n<h3>The fall brought knowledge of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:22\">GEN 3:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:4-Gen3:7\">GEN 3:4–3:7</a></p>\n<h3>The OT law exposed the nature of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:7\">ROM 7:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:20\">ROM 3:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:15\">ROM 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:13\">ROM 5:13</a></p>\n<h2>Human ignorance does not excuse sin</h2>\n<h3>By individuals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:17-Lev5:19\">LEV 5:17–5:19</a></strong> <em>The law made provision for atonement of sins committed as a result of ignorance.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:27-Lev4:35\">LEV 4:27–4:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:27-Num15:29\">NUM 15:27–15:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:20\">EZK 45:20</a></p>\n<h3>By the nation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:13-Lev4:21\">LEV 4:13–4:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:22-Num15:26\">NUM 15:22–15:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:7\">HEB 9:7</a></p>\n<h3>By leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:22-Lev4:26\">LEV 4:22–4:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:3-Lev4:12\">LEV 4:3–4:12</a></p>\n<h2>Sin committed in ignorance incurs a lesser judgment than other sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:47-Luke12:48\">LUK 12:47–12:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:12\">PRO 24:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:14-Rom2:15\">ROM 2:14–2:15</a></p>\n<h2>Repentance of sin committed in ignorance brings forgiveness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:1-Gen20:18\">GEN 20:1–20:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:17-Acts3:20\">ACT 3:17–3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:13\">1TI 1:13</a></p>\n<h2>Ignorance of God and salvation</h2>\n<h3>There is no salvation outside Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:12\">ACT 4:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:6\">JHN 14:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:5-1Tim2:6\">1TI 2:5–2:6</a></p>\n<h3>Believers have a responsibility to remove ignorance of the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:14-Rom10:17\">ROM 10:14–10:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:19–28:20</a></p>\n<h2>Ignorance and God's judgment</h2>\n<h3>The justice of God in salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:25\">GEN 18:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:4\">DEU 32:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:33\">NEH 9:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:12\">PRO 24:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:37\">DAN 4:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:47-Luke12:48\">LUK 12:47–12:48</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment falls on all who do not know him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:8-2Thess1:10\">2TH 1:8–1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:6\">PSA 79:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:25\">JER 10:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:8\">ROM 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment falls severely on those who choose to disobey him</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:28-Prov1:32\">PRO 1:28–1:32</a> <em>on Israel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:29-Acts17:31\">ACT 17:29–17:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:2-Heb2:3\">HEB 2:2–2:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:20-2Pet2:22\">2PE 2:20–2:22</a></p>",
